&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Care Act Assessor (Band 4) – Stafford Adult Social Care Team (37.5hrs per week)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 4 Care Act Assessors in the Adult Social Care Team. The posts will be based at Stafford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicants will be working within a busy assessment, care management and review team. Both roles will involve working closely with service-users, carers, partner agencies and other professionals providing low level assessment of need, signposting, care planning and reviews in line with The Care Act (2014) and Mental Capacity Act (2005). &lt;br /&gt; The Trust is committed to safeguarding and promoting the welfare of children and young people/vulnerable adults and expects all staff to share this commitment. The Trust is also committed to professional development and will provide opportunities for training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is highly desirable for the candidate to have previous experience of working with vulnerable adults or adults with a disability in a community setting and proficient computer skills are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; The successful applicants will need to be able to travel across Staffordshire and when required out of county. You will require a clean driving license and a vehicle for business use.&lt;br /&gt; If you would like to discuss this post informally please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jemma Darlington Tel: &lt;span&gt;01782 137049&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;or email &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Jemma.Darlington@mpft.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
